{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, suppose one wants to diagnose patients based on a textual description of their symptoms.",
    "Some aspects of this data may indeed be privacysensitive, such as characteristics of the patient.",
    "However, basic aspects like grammar and syntax are not privacy-sensitive.",
    "By training a model privately from scratch, we are treating everything as private.",
    "To overcome these obstacles, it is possible to use public data."
  ]
}